Why observability?
===============

	Q. Unfortunately your app is running slow, why?

	Ø Server cpu
	Ø Server logs
	Ø Restart the app

	Ø In modern technology all app's are running in modern systems, we used basic monitoring 
	Ø Something is broken in the server

But modern systems are:
=====================

	1. microservices'  - all e-commerce app's
	2. Containers
	3. Kubernetes
	4. Distributed systems 

	Ø When something breaks , it is very difficult to know the root cause.

That's why we need observability 

What is observability?
==================

	Ø It is nothing but the ability to understand wt is happening inside a system by looking its outputs - metrics, logs and traces.


Monitoring :- it will tell you what happened 
Observability:- it will tell you why it happened


Observability four golden signals 
===========================

Latency:- user open a browser the fast response time is 10 secs but it is responding in 15 sec , there is a problem is called latency  - how fast system responds

Traffic:- how many requests your system is receiving , 100 - 500 req/sec, 1000 - 5000 req/sec, if traffic suddenly increases --> system can crash - how many users are accessing

Errors:- how many requests are failing , if error rate increases --> system will become unhealthy - how many requests fail

Saturation :- how full your system resources are :- cpu, memory, disk, network - how much system resources are used.

